column2: Ice mostly out- some block ice left- temp 36- cloudy- west wind of 5 mph- 12 wood ducks- but only 3 hens- immature eagle harassing wood ducks yesterday.
Cloudy- no wind- air temp 58- humidity 56%- black fly explosion.
Partly sunny- air temp 63- south breeze- most of the leaves are out.
Air temp 75- SE wind 5 mph- barometer  30.02- sunny- 10 mallards + woodducks
Partly cloudy- light E wind- 4" rain since Thursday- ducklings- orioles- sapsuckers- woodpeckers
Air temp 75- 72% humidity- pressure 29.62"- light S wind- overcast- mallards half grown- much foliage growth
Air temp 70- W wind- overcast- ducklings 2/3 grown- fishing terrible- bugs
Light E wind- overcast- air temp 71- clouds of mosquitoes- first hatch ducks full size- second hatch 1-2 weeks old
Clear sky- air temp 75- 10mph W wind- less boat traffic this summer- but bigger boats and wakes
Air temp 74- slight SE breeze- humidity 68%- much boating- sediment stirred up
Sediments stirred up- overcast- air temp 78- humidity 78%- no wind
Partly cloudy- S breeze- air temp 74- humidity 70%- morning fog burns off early- poor fishing all season
Cool- 55 degrees- W wind.  I week ago observed algae cloud on a calm evening.  None since.  Only 25 mallards still here.  But weather has been great.
Sunny- clear- 75 degrees S wind.  Humidity is 65%.  Beautiful day- considering it has been in the 30's the last 2 nights.  25- 30 mallard ducks still on the lake.
Clear and cold- 42 degrees.  Pretty bright day.  Leaves are starting to turn.  Ducks still here.  Saw 1 woodcock and no birds yesterday.  Fishing is good.
Partly sunny- light NW wind- 34 degrees.  20-30 ducks come in cautiously to eat cover each day.
Ice off on 4/15/94.  Today 1" rain in morning.  Now 73 degrees- partly sunny- SW breeze- nice day.  Have wood ducks nesting in both houses.  Also hooded merganser in dump nesting.
Partly cloudy- 70 degrees- W breeze- nice day.  Late on memorial day we got hail stones from golf ball size to 2.5" across.  Fishing is bad.  We are paying the price of spearing spawning females.
78 degrees + 70% humidity- cloudy- light breeze.  A few mallard hens have 3 ducklings.  One has 16- not all the same size.  Big Mayfly hatch.  Feeding baby ducks + robins.
Sunny- light breeze- 80 degrees.  Ducks are still hatching- but only about 3/nest.  Everything else is growing.  So far a beautiful summer.
Breeze from se- 67 degrees- no bugs on water- sunny.  New people on lake enjoying a beautiful day.  All but one hen mallard have 3 ducklings-strange.
SE breeze- overcast- 68 degrees.  Dreary day- but sure beats winter.
Slight breeze- 75 degrees- cloudy.  Little boat traffic except for the damnable seadoos.  They should be banned state-wide.
Partly cloudy- almost calm- 70 degrees.  Little boat traffic.  Saw 2/3 hatch of wood ducks yesterday.  Mallards growing fast.  Fishing is still terrible.
Brown algae May be developing.  Westerly wind at 10 mph.  Partly cloudy- thunderheads- severe storms predicted.  75 degrees- nice day.  Water level: summer normal
Water is a little darker- but do not see algae.  Nice day- 70 degrees- light wind- partly cloudy.  Has been cold + wet.  We had 3" of rain last Tuesday night.
Overcast- 70 degrees + 70% humidity- pressure falling- no wind.  No one on the lake.  Most of the ducks are flying.
Cloudy- light NE breeze- 52 degrees.  There are more ducks (30) waiting to be fed at home than I saw hunting up river today.
Partly cloudy- E wind- 64 degrees- low 50 degrees.  Very nice day- but leaves are mostly down.
Clear- 68 degrees- light westerly breeze.  Wood duck + mallards nesting - opening day fishing   lake heavily ( ) again by ( ) .
Light westerly breeze- 80 degrees- partly cloudy- very little boat traffic.
Westerly wind- partly cloudy- pressure dropping- temp. 90 degrees- humidity 65%.  A move slow day.
Temp. 73 degrees- cloudy- so breeze- boat traffic up- fishing way down.  We nee rain- streams are low.  Not many clouds.
Lake warmer than 68 degree air temp. (at surface) .  Overcast- humidity 100%- 2.6" rain last 2 days.  Little breeze.  Ground water table is down 4'.
Partly cloudy- no wind- 76 degrees- humidity- 70 degrees.  Nice day.  Little boat traffic.  Good day for fishing if we had any.
Light gray algae.  Clear- 78 degrees- humidity 62%- light westerly breeze.  Beautiful day on the lake- 85 degrees up on the ( ) marsh and a million flies.  Water level normal due to recent rain.
Water is clear for this lake.  78 degrees- humidity 70%.  Light W breeze- partly cloudy- very pleasant day.  Light gray or white algae on shrimp
Lake froze over 11-9-95. Ice is still on except out front to the island. In 5 days it will be 6 months. Mallards woodies are here-nice day. Cloudy no wind 50 degrees. Opening of fishing.
Overcast day- east wind again but no rain yet. we have greened up but still is dry. birds and ducks are all here.
Beautiful- 72 degrees- slight breeze- 60 % humidity. foliage is out. buds everywhere. could this be spring
Beautiful day- 60% humidity- 75 degrees temp.- 10-15 mph W wind. yesterday 90 degree temp. 82% humidity. looks like a good duck hatch! no walleye!
Partly cloudy- light W breeze- 82 degrees- 60% humidity. good duck hatch. with the fireworks the loons were quiet last night.

Water clear for this time of year. clear 70 degrees- southerly breeze- fireweed + day lily in bloom- yellow finch are brilliant. young orioles and rose breasted grossbeak at feeder. some young duck hatches this past week.
60 degrees + overcast- some water skiers- 4 ducks with ducklings.
Hazy day- 76 degrees- SE breeze- falling barometer. I got up this morning to the sound of ducks calling down by the point. then still-then the distant sound of loons laughing. very nice.

81 degrees- east-southeast breeze 10 mph- 70% humidity- partly cloudy- nice day. Except for jet skis it's been quiet on the lake. could it be that when jet skis move in they chase all the watercraft away
68 degrees- slight haze- water skiers- float boats and jet skiers- not as busy as normal vacation season.
Clouds- overcast and cool (52 degrees) . took old dog- Simba- age 13 hunting yesterday. he got five birds up and was happy. he's a little sore today.
Algal bloom off 3 days prior to sample-air temp. 60 degrees. 60% fall color- beautiful + peaceful.
Too cold for swimming. no traffic on lake-partly sunny-wind 10 to 15 mph.
Ice went out on 5-1-97.  Mallards- woodducks common mergansers- were here immediately.  No fish to catch.
Sunny with a temperature of 60 degrees- 10 mph wind from northeast- trees in bud- no fish- and very few boats.

The temperature is 66 degrees.  Sunny with few clouds.  Wind 12 to 21 mph.  Two fishing boats- no one skiing. white caps on lake.  Not many people outside- a number of piers and boats not in the water yet.
Partly cloudy- 74 degrees- 60% humidity- high pressure- slight breeze from se. little boat traffic or fishing.  Mayfly hatch but no ducklings.
Temperature 80 degrees- sunny- no wind- quiet. one mallard hatch.  A few more boats and song birds.
Cloud cover- little breeze.  Jet skis and water skis stirring up the water.  73 degrees- humidity 68%.

The temperature is 84 degrees.  Sunny- some high clouds- little wind- eight personal water crafts- two skiers- four fishing boats- two pontoons on lake.  Water very high.  Heavy rains in the last two days.
Half grown ducks were eating grass clippings next to the lake when a big eagle landed.  Lots of excitement.
The temperature is 72 degrees.  Cloudy- wind variable 4-8 mph.  Very little traffic on lake- two PWC's- one skier- three fishing boats- two pontoons.
Sediment stirred up by jet skis running close to shore.  Nice day- 78 degrees- light breeze- partly cloudy- fishing no longer a sport.
Partly sunny- 76 degrees- SW breeze- 3 inches of rain last couple of days.  A nice labor day.- most of the ducks are mature- not as many as last year.
No algae this week.  Last week we did have a green algal bloom.
10 mph wind from the northwest.  40 degrees and cloudy.  Still have 20 mallards and 1 black duck  on the lake.  Lake will freeze in 30 days.
Lake was cold- 50 degrees- air temperature was 40 degrees- no other traffic on the lake.
Cool temperature but a nice day- winds are calm- and sunny.
Very nice day- sunny- and calm
Lake froze over Nov. 17- Ice is 9 inch thick. There is

column1: about 2 inch. of snow on the ground.

column2: A very nice day with light winds from the west Temp.

column1: Ice went out on April 15 @ 11.40 am.

column2: Nice day and looks like a good Memorial day weekend.
It was a wonderful day- clear and sunny 88 deg.
It is a HOT day- but great weather.
It was a very nice day- but still HOT weather here.
It is a very nice day. Light wind out of the NW. Sunny
Nice fall day- but a cool wind on the lake. Air temp
It was a windy day here. We had some strong winds and heavy rain around 7 pm.
It was a nice day on our lake. many people enjoying the northern Wis. lakes.

It was an overcast day and we even got a light rain ! This was the first rain in over 3 weeks. The lake water is low and also getting very clear. Today I noticed that the lake trafic is low as the summer comes to and end.
A normal early fall day in northern Wis..
It was a nice fall day. The wind was calm and most of the fall leaves are down.

column1: I guess "Old man winter" is not far away !

column2: It was a nice day for the early part of Nov.- and I thought I would do one more temp. test before I take my boat out for the winter.

column1: We had calm winds and the air temp. was 42.8 Deg.s F.

Our lake had a good summer. The water levels dropped to one of the lowest I have seen in over 50 yr.s. The fall rains have brought the level back up to normal now. The weatherman is calling for snow in the next few days. So I guess the summer season is over.

column2: Lake open on April 24. I was clear of water by April 27

column1: Air Temp. was a blammy 34 Degs. at time of testing.

column2: It was a nice day. A little on the cool side.
A very nice and calm day. With warm sun and fall colors to enjoy.
It was a very nice day on the lake.
Warm temp.s and couldn't be a nicer day on the lake.
A very nice day  on our lake.
A wonderful day on the lake. Water level is hight due to heavy rains. Water has darken from run off of streams into lake.
A cooler day on the lake- but still very nice .
Very nice fall day- leaves are in good color.

column1: Our lake is a good 12 inch above normal from last few heavy rains in the area. Many docks are under water or floating.  Very nice fall day- leaves are in good color.
Our lake is a good 12 inch above normal from last few heavy rains in the area. Many docks are under water or floating.

column2: A wonderful day - but still on the cold side these days.
Overcast day with rain to come this week.
A perfect day for any activity on the Lake.
Nice weather- but on the cool side. But it is also early in April.
A very nice day- almost perfect.
A very wonderful day to be out on the water.
A perfect day to be on the lake.
A bit on the over cast- but otherwise a nice day.
Nice day- but on the cool side.
The ice is gone and it is a wonderful day in the northwoods.

The weather conditions for lake monitoring were overcast with a slight breeze and a temperature of approximately 60 degrees Fahrenheit. Using the bathymetric map (Figure 2)- we navigated to the approximate deep hole of the lake. Due to the unavailability of our DO meter- we were not able to take dissolved oxygen and temperature readings. At the deep hole site we obtained a Secchi disk reading and performed spiny water flea and zebra mussel veliger tows. We then went to another site to perform a second zebra mussel veliger tow.  Findings: Secchi Disk:

column1: Lake Thompson was brown colored with low algae levels which resulted in a Secchi disk reading of 5 feet at a depth of 23 feet- recorded at the approximate deep hole location.

After data collection- we went to three locations on the lake shore to perform an AIS presence/absence check. For the three locations of AIS presence/absence checks- we meandered the shoreline via walking- using an aquascope to eliminate the glare on the water surface. We looked through vegetation and checked under and around solid surfaces. Findings: We did not find any new invasive species during our lake monitoring. We found a few dead shells of Chinese mystery snails and a couple purple loosestrife plants at the public boat landing that have already been reported on this lake. SWF and ZM were not discovered in this waterbody.  Report by Steph Boismenue

column2: With all the rain our lake is way above normal.
Lake water levels are very high from all the rain we have had.

Another nice day on our lake. We have around 35 to 40 Canadian Geese on our lake this year. Some residents don't like them as they are pooping on the lawns ! We also have  3 to 4 pairs of Loons. One pair has two babies- with mom and dad watching over.
